### Describe the bug

When accessing a list using an index inside an if statement embedded in a class attribute I receive an ArgumentOutOfRangeException:

```csharp
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Home Page";

    List<int> numbers = new List<int>() { 1, 2, 3 };
}

@for (int counter = 0; counter < numbers.Count; counter++)
{
    <div class="field-grp form-group @if(numbers[counter] > 2){<text>hidden</text>} col-12 col-sm-auto last">
        <h1>Some HTML</h1>
    </div>
}
```

It appears the if statement is being evaluated after the for loop has been completed and the counter has been incremented past the index top range.

### Expected Behavior

No exception is thrown

### Steps To Reproduce

Here is a public repo on GitHub to show the issue:

https://github.com/KenBrannigan/AspNetCoreListViewBug

All I did was create a .NET 6 ASP.NET Core MVC project and added the following code to the Index view:

```csharp
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Home Page";

    List<int> numbers = new List<int>() { 1, 2, 3 };
}

@for (int counter = 0; counter < numbers.Count; counter++)
{
    <div class="field-grp form-group @if(numbers[counter] > 2){<text>hidden</text>} col-12 col-sm-auto last">
        <h1>Some HTML</h1>
    </div>
}
```

### Exceptions (if any)

I receive the following exception:

ArgumentOutOfRangeException: Index was out of range. Must be non-negative and less than the size of the collection. (Parameter 'index')

### .NET Version

6

### Anything else?

ASP.NET Core 6 MVC Application running in Visual Studio 2022 17.5.2

I am able to work around the issue by changing the code to:

```csharp
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Home Page";

    List<int> numbers = new List<int>() { 1, 2, 3 };
}

@for (int counter = 0; counter < numbers.Count; counter++)
{
    <div class="field-grp form-group @(numbers[counter] > 2 ? "hidden" : string.Empty)</text>} col-12 col-sm-auto last">
        <h1>Some HTML</h1>
    </div>
}
```

I also tested using ASP.NET Core 7 and I get the same error.

